e=\"box-sizing: inherit; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235);\"><td style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 8px 8px 8px 16px; vertical-align: top;\"><code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3);\">or</code></td><td style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 8px; vertical-align: top;\">OR</td><td style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 8px; vertical-align: top;\"><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn btnsmall btnsmall\" href=\"/learn-python/21/try-it/demo_precedence_or\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 1px 10px 2px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; float: right; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif;\">Try it </a></td></tr></tbody></table><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">If two operators have the same precedence, the expression is evaluated from left to right.</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Addition&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3);\">+</code>&nbsp;and subtraction&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3);\">-</code>&nbsp;has the same precedence, and therefor we evaluate the expression from left to right:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\">5</span>&nbsp;+&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\">4</span>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\">7</span>&nbsp;+&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\">3</span>)<br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"/learn-python/21/try-it/demo_precedence_same\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Run example </a></div>', '0', 0, 0, '2023-06-14 23:54:26.000000', '2023-10-09 20:37:17.448587');
INSERT INTO `questions_learn` (`id`, `title`, `slug`, `description`, `codes`, `search_count`, `is_input_required`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(22, 'Python Lists', 'python-lists', '<div class=\"w3-codeline notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: white; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; padding: 15px; border-left-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 15px;\">mylist = [<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span>]<br></div><hr style=\"margin-right: -16px; margin-left: -16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">List</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">Lists are used to store multiple items in a single variable.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em;\"><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Lists are one of 4 built-in data types in Python used to store collections of data, the other 3 are Tuple, Set, and Dictionary, all with&nbsp;different qualities and usage.</span></font></p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">Lists are created using square brackets:</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example<br></h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Create a List:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">thislist = [<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span>]<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(thislist)<br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"/learn-python/22/try-it/demo_list\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself </a></div><hr style=\"margin-right: -16px; margin-left: -16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">List Items</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">List items are ordered, changeable, and allow duplicate values.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">List items are indexed, the first item has index&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3);\">[0]</code>, the second item has index&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3);\">[1]</code>&nbsp;etc.</p><hr style=\"margin-right: -16px; margin-left: -16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Ordered</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">When we say that lists are ordered, it means that the items have a defined order, and that order will not change.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">If you add new items to a list, the new items will be placed at the end of the list.</p><div class=\"w3-panel w3-note\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 16px 32px; margin: 24px -32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 204); border-left: none;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;\">Note:</span><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;There are some list methods that&nbsp;will change the order, but in general: the order of the items will not change.</span></font></p></div><hr style=\"margin-right: -16px; margin-left: -16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Changeable</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">The list is changeable, meaning that we can change, add, and remove items in a list after it has been created.</p><hr style=\"margin-right: -16px; margin-left: -16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Allow Duplicates</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">Since lists are indexed, lists can have items with the same value:</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Lists allow duplicate values:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43)