ringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span>))&nbsp;<span class=\"commentcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: green;\"># note the double round-brackets<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"></span><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(thislist)<br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"/learn-python/22/try-it/demo_list_constructor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself </a></div><hr style=\"margin-right: -16px; margin-left: -16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Python Collections (Arrays)</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">There are four collection data types in the Python programming language:</p><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;\">List</span>&nbsp;is a collection which is ordered and changeable. Allows duplicate members.</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><b>Tuple&nbsp;</b>is a collection which is ordered and unchangeable. Allows duplicate members.</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><b>Set&nbsp;</b>is a collection which is unordered, unchangeable*, and unindexed. No duplicate members.</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><b>Dictionary&nbsp;</b>is a collection which is ordered** and changeable. No duplicate members.</li></ul><div class=\"w3-panel w3-note\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 16px 32px; margin: 24px -32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 204); border-left: none; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">*Set&nbsp;<em style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">items</em>&nbsp;are unchangeable, but you can remove and/or add items whenever you like.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">**As of Python version 3.7, dictionaries are&nbsp;<em style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">ordered</em>. In Python 3.6 and earlier, dictionaries are&nbsp;<em style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">unordered</em>.</p></div><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">When choosing a collection type, it is useful to understand the properties of that type. Choosing the right type for a particular data set could mean retention of meaning, and, it could mean an increase in efficiency or security.</p>', '0', 0, 0, '2023-06-15 00:01:13.000000', '2023-10-09 20:56:23.200834'),
(23, 'Python - Access List Items', 'python-access-list-items', '<h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Access Items</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">List items are indexed and you can access them by referring to the index number:</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example<br></h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Print the second item of the list:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">thislist = [<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span>]<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(thislist[<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\">1</span>])<br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"/learn-python/23/try-it/demo_list_access\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself </a></div><div class=\"w3-panel w3-note\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 16px 32px; margin: 24px -32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 204); border-left: none; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;\">Note:&nbsp;</span>The first item has index 0.</p></div><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Negative Indexing</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">Negative indexing means start from the end</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3);\">-1</code>&nbsp;refers to the last item,&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3);\">-2</code>&nbsp;refers to the second last item etc.</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Print the last item of the list:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">thislist = [<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span>]<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(thislist[-<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\">1</span>])<br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"/learn-python/23/try-it/demo_list_negative_index\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself </a></div><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Range of Indexes</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">You can specify a range of indexes by specifying where to start and where to end the range.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">When specifying a range, the return value will be a new list with the specified items.</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Return the third, fourth, and fifth item:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">thislist = [<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"orange\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"kiwi\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"melon\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"mango\"</span>]<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(thislist[<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\">2</span>:<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\">5</span>])<br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"/learn-python/23/try-it/demo_list_range\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself </a></div><div class=\"w3-panel w3-note\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 16px 32px; margin: 24px -32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 204); border-left: none; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;\">Note:</span>&nbsp;The search will start at index 2 (included) and end at index 5 (not included).</p></div><div class=\"w3-panel w3-note\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 16px 32px; margin: 24px -32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 204); border-left: none; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Remember that the first item has index 0.</p></div><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">By leaving out the start value, the range will start at the first item:</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">This example returns the items from the beginning to, but NOT including, \"kiwi\":</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">thislist = [<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"orange\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"kiwi\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"melon\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"mango\"</span>]<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(thislist[:<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\">4</span>])<br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"/learn-python/23/try-it/demo_list_range2\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself </a></div><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">By leaving out the end value, the range will go on to the end of the list:</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">This example returns the items from \"cherry\" to the end:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">thislist = [<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"orange\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"kiwi\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"melon\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"mango\"</span>]<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(thislist[<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\">2</span>:])<br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"/learn-python/23/try-it/demo_list_range3\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself </a></div><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Range of Negative Indexes</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">Specify negative indexes if you want to start the search from the end of the list:</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">This example returns the items from \"orange\" (-4) to, but NOT including \"mango\" (-1):</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">thislist = [<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"orange\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"kiwi\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"melon\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"mango\"</span>]<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(thislist[-<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\">4</span>:-<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\">1</span>])<br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"/learn-python/23/try-it/demo_list_range_negative\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: