(35, 'Python - Update Tuples', 'python-update-tuples', '<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">Tuples are unchangeable, meaning that you cannot change, add, or remove items once the tuple is created.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">But there are some workarounds.</p><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Change Tuple Values</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">Once a tuple is created, you cannot change its values. Tuples are&nbsp;<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;\">unchangeable</span>, or&nbsp;<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;\">immutable</span>&nbsp;as it also is called.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">But there is a workaround. You can convert the tuple into a list, change the list, and convert the list back into a tuple.</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example<br></h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Convert the tuple into a list to be able to change it:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">x = (<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span>)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">y =&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">list</span>(x)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">y[<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\">1</span>] =&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"kiwi\"</span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">x =&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">tuple</span>(y)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(x)<br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"/learn-python/35/try-it/demo_tuple_change\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself </a></div><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Add Items</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">Since tuples are immutable, they do not have a built-in&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3);\">append()</code>&nbsp;method, but there are other ways to add items to a tuple.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">1.&nbsp;<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;\">Convert into a list</span>: Just like the workaround for<em style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp;changing&nbsp;</em>a tuple, you can convert it into a list, add your item(s), and convert it back into a tuple.</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Convert the tuple into a list, add \"orange\", and convert it back into a tuple:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\"><span class=\"pythoncolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: black;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">thistuple = (</span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">,&nbsp;</span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">,&nbsp;</span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">)</span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">y =&nbsp;</span><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">list</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">(thistuple)</span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">y.append(</span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"orange\"</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">)</span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">thistuple =&nbsp;</span><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"></span><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">tuple</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">(y)</span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"></span></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"/learn-python/35/try-it/demo_tuple_add_orange\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself </a></div><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">2.&nbsp;<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;\">Add tuple to a tuple</span>. You are allowed to add tuples to tuples, so if you want to add one item, (or many), create a new tuple with the item(s), and add it to the existing tuple:</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Create a new tuple with the value \"orange\", and add that tuple:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\"><span class=\"pythoncolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: black;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">thistuple = (</span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">,&nbsp;</span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">,&nbsp;</span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">)</span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">y = (</span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"orange\"</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">,)</span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">thistuple += y</span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"></span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">(thistuple)</span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"></span></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"/learn-python/35/try-it/demo_tuple_add_tuple\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself </a></div><div class=\"w3-panel w3-note\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 16px 32px; margin: 24px -32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 204); border-left: none; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;\">Note:</span>&nbsp;When creating a tuple with only one item, remember to include a comma after the item, otherwise it will not be identified as a tuple.</p></div><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Remove Items</h2><div class=\"w3-panel w3-note\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 16px 32px; margin: 24px -32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 204); border-left: none; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;\">Note:</span>&nbsp;You cannot remove items in a tuple.</p></div><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">Tuples are&nbsp;<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;\">unchangeable</span>, so you cannot remove items from it, but you can use the same workaround as we used for changing and adding tuple items:</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Convert the tuple into a list, remove \"apple\", and convert it back into a tuple:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\"><span class=\"pythoncolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: black;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">thistuple = (</span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">,&nbsp;</span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">,&nbsp;</span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">)</span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">y =&nbsp;</span><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">list</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">(thistuple)</span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">y.remove(</span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">)</span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">thistuple =&nbsp;</span><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"></span><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">tuple</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">(y)</span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"></span></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"/learn-python/35/try-it/demo_tuple_remove\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself </a></div><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">Or you can delete the tuple completely:</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">The&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3);\">del</code>&nbsp;keyword can delete the tuple completely:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">thistuple = (<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span>)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">del</span>&nbsp;thistuple<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(thistuple)<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"commentcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: green;\">#this will raise an error because the tuple no longer exists</span><br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"/learn-python/35/try-it/demo_tuple_del\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself </a></div>', '0', 0, 0, '2023-06-15 01:06:31.000000', '2023-10-11 17:37:58.200903'),
(36, 'Python - Unpack Tuples', 'python-unpack-tuples', '<h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Unpacking a Tuple</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">When we create a tuple, we normally assign values to it. This is called \"packing\" a tuple:</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example<br></h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Packing a tuple:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\"><span class=\"pythoncolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: black;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">fruits = (</span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">,&nbsp;</span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">,&nbsp;</span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">)</span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span></span></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"/learn-python/36/try-it/demo_tuple_packing\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself </a></div><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">But, in Python, we are also allowed to extract the values back into variables. This is called \"unpacking\":</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Unpacking a tuple:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">fruits = (<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span>)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span>(green, yellow, red) = fruits<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(green)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(yellow)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(red)<br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"/learn-python/36/try-it/demo_tuple_unpacking\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself </a></div><div class=\"w3-panel w3-note\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 16px 32px; margin: 24px -32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 204); border-left: none; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;\">Note:</span>&nbsp;The number of variables must match the number of values in the tuple, if not, you must use an asterisk to collect the remaining values as a list.</p></div><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-seri